<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> “Non-Lethal Swimmer Neutralization Study”; Applied Research Laboratories; <a href="/wiki/University_of_Texas_at_Austin" title="University of Texas at Austin">University of Texas at Austin</a>; G2 Software Systems, Inc., <a href="/wiki/San_Diego" title="San Diego">San Diego</a>; TECHNICAL DOCUMENT 3138; May 2002 <a href="http://64.233.169.104/unclesam?q=cache:s2NL05udytgJ:www.spawar.navy.mil/sti/publications/pubs/td/3138/td3138cond.pdf+electromagnetic+weapons+affect+heart+rhythm&amp;hl=en&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=5&amp;gl=us" class="external autonumber" title="http://64.233.169.104/unclesam?q=cache:s2NL05udytgJ:www.spawar.navy.mil/sti/publications/pubs/td/3138/td3138cond.pdf+electromagnetic+weapons+affect+heart+rhythm&amp;hl=en&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=5&amp;gl=us" rel="nofollow">[3]</a></li>
